.TH "bcm63xx_set_stall" 9 "bcm63xx_set_stall" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bcm63xx_set_stall \- Enable/disable stall on one endpoint.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" bcm63xx_set_stall
.BI "(struct bcm63xx_udc *udc "  ","
.BI "struct bcm63xx_ep *bep "  ","
.BI "bool is_stalled "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "udc" 12
Reference to the device controller.
.IP "bep" 12
Endpoint on which to operate.
.IP "is_stalled" 12
true to enable stall, false to disable.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
See notes in \fBbcm63xx_update_wedge\fP regarding automatic clearing of
halt/stall conditions.
